==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tetanin
<hw>Tet"a*nin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A poisonous base (ptomaine) formed in meat broth
through the agency of a peculiar microbe from the wound of a person who
has died of tetanus; -- so called because it produces tetanus as one of
its prominent effects.</def> <-- ?? not in Merck INdex -- tetanospasmin?
The neurotoxin of Clostridium tetani. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

